Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 5 YEARS, with credit for 172 days. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 1/2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 1/2 YEARS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION (if revoked):
*Serve 6 months in the House of Correction with release to the Day Reporting Center-STAYED until 7-13-15,5pm.  Defendant instructed to report to HOC.
*No controlled substances or alcohol;
*AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
*Urine screens- the Court recommends revocation upon any dirty urine analysis;
*Seek and maintain employment;
*Participate in job and vocational training;
*Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
* No contact with victim Tiffany L., or co-actor William D. Goodrum;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $573.00 payable to Tiffany L- joint and several with William D. Goodrum (15CF1089).  If revoked, the Court ordered all financial obligations and restitution to be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Appeal rights given.
